In this article, the author, Jill, expresses their belief in the sacred obligation the nation has towards veterans and their families. They highlight the importance of providing veterans with tools and resources for economic opportunity, security, and dignity. The author states that the current approach by the Administration is working, with the unemployment rate for veterans at a record low of 2.4 percent, down from an average of 6.5 percent in 2020. They also note that unemployment rates for veterans of all backgrounds, including white, Black, Asian, and Hispanic veterans, have decreased and are now the same or lower than their nonveteran counterparts in 2021. Additionally, the unemployment rate for veterans with a service-connected disability has declined to 3.4 percent. The author attributes this progress to the Administration's efforts to rebuild the economy from the bottom up and the middle out. They mention initiatives to bring veterans into critical industries like trucking and ensure they have access to good-paying, quality jobs. The article concludes by stating that the Administration is committed to reducing the costs veterans and working families face.